nomic and racial disparities in health care were exacerbated by bad policies regarding everything from zoning to education to environmental regulation. The study further chronicles how New Jersey struggled to deal with public health crises like the AIDS epidemic and the crack epidemic. Yet it also explores how the state has developed some of the nation’s most innovative responses to public health challenges, and then provides policy suggestions for how we might build an even healthier New Jersey.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aenvironment, government, policy, public policy, health policy, health, health care, medicine, new jersey, garden state, cancer, cancer alley, cancer cluster, covid-19, corona virus, pandemic, inequality, class, race, pollution.1 aSchneider, Dona, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishz978311131925408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023z9783111318677oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883204640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978832046423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978832046/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131925-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-al